Puerto Rican legislators who want their island to become a state said Monday they would try to override a veto of a bill they believe will help resolve the territory 's relationship to the United States .
Gov . Anibal Acevedo Vila on Sunday vetoed the bill , which would have asked Washington to honor any eventual decision for the island to become a state , increase its autonomy or become independent .
QN : Do Puerto Rico lawmakers aim to override the governor 's veto ?

Marburg virus is a highly fatal pathogen spread through direct body contact .
It attacks the gastrointestinal tract and kills rapidly .
It has an incubation period of three to nine days with most deaths occurring within one week after the onset of symptoms .
